added.title: Diamondhead AW3: Enemies Unite
added.description: In the wake of civil war, the Petrosapiens, Subsapiens, and Antrosapiens unite against a new, unknown adversary invading their home world: the ferocious Fulmini!

added.title: Heatblast AW3: The Fast and the Fiery
added.description: A Kineceleran delegation visits Pyros to discuss diplomacy and ends up in a heated game of Fireball, the Pyronites' planetary pastime, now kicked up a notch thanks to their speedster guests.

added.title: Cannonbolt AW3: Beach Bro Brouhaha
added.description: It's beach season on Arburia again, and the Pelarotas must contend with a crowd of the most obtrusive tourists in the Omniverse, Vaxasaurians- only to find common ground over their shared appreciation for making a splash.

added.title: Shock Rock AW3: Spaceships in the Night
added.description: After tearing apart their planet with an overconcentration of hoarded energy, the Fulmini christen their mothership 'Fulmas II' and set their sights on Khoros, only to find the Tetramands are out on their own invasion- of Fulmas!

added.title: Rath AW3: Endless Party Planet
added.description: On vacation from their war-torn home world, the Petropians travel to Appoplexia and use crystalline constructs to keep the fun-loving feline locals on their toes.

added.title: Humungousaur AW3: Planetary Pin
added.description: The Appoplexians journey to Terradino for a gladiatorial tournament hosted by the Vaxasaurians- an epic clash of tail and claw that will rumble the entire Omniverse!

added.title: Four Arms AW3: The Stenchening Cometh
added.description: The Tetramands encounter their greatest and most pungent threat yet— a swarm of Lepidopterrans, whose agile aerobatics and acrid aroma make them a rare match for their formidable four-armed foes!

added.title: Slapback AW3: Population Override
added.description: The Ekoplektoids' amoebic ability to multiply their own cells and subdivide into smaller, denser clones leads to out-of-control overpopulation, forcing them on a space expedition for more space.

added.title: XLR8 AW3: The Slow Age
added.description: After centuries of failing to break their own land-speed records, the Kinecelerans put an end to "The Slow Age" by teaming up with the Arburian Pelarotas.

added.title: Stinkfly AW3: Strange Snow
added.description: The Lepidopterrans find their most famous mountain range covered in a strange snow— seemingly overnight— that turns out to be a deluge of endlessly multiplying (and downsizing) Ekoplektoids.

added.title: Heatblast AW2: Cold Snap
added.description: Join the Pyronites as they ring in the holidays with a special tradition that would make even the most warm-blooded of visitors go crazy from the heat— racing to the top of Mount Helios, an active volcano!

added.title: Upgrade AW1: Crisis on Galvan B
added.description: Once devoid of natural life, Galvan B. was upgraded seemingly overnight after a Galvan terraform experiment accidentally crashed into the moon's surface. Relive the birth of the Galvanic Mechamorphs as they rise from the impact site and terraform their surroundings into the lush techno-organic moon we see today.

added.title: Wildvine AW1: Wild Siders
added.description: Flors Verdana, green with vegetation, is as wild and abundant as the Florauna that inhabit it. Let's take a walk on the wild side as the plant-based aliens trade admiring the planet's lush beauty for the dangerous thrill of waking a sleeping giant.

added.title: XLR8 AW2: Speed Round
added.description: The Kinecelerans live life at the fastest pace possible, even when they're letting off steam— hence their supercharged take on what we Earthlings call hockey, where every point is more electrifying than the last!

added.title: Overflow AW1: The Pirates of Cascareau
added.description: The torrential surface of the water planet Cascareau forces us undersea, but luckily, this is where all the swashbuckling action is! Let's navigate the watery depths as the Cascans fend off fellow pirates & vicious Leviathans on their quest for a bounty of Serpent Glass, the raw material needed to construct their exoskeleton.

added.title: Wildvine AW2: The Worldtree
added.description: The Verda World Tree gives life to the entire ecosystem surrounding it, but like any organic matter, this magnificent specimen has a life cycle of its own. That's where the Florauna come in, herding wild Mushroars, gigantic pollen beetles, to fertilize the wilting tree in time for a blooming spring.

added.title: XLR8 AW1: Gauntlet of Gliders
added.description: Kinet, a planet dominated by electrical storms, is home to the lightning quick Kinecelerans! To combat the inclement weather, younglings must complete the Running of the Gauntlet, a most epic retrieval of the gliders worn on their feet. Traversing the desolate terrain at high speeds to reach the lair of a Kinet Molluscarx, the young ones must obtain the creature's precious pearl if they are to fulfill this Kineceleran rite of passage.

added.title: Stinkfly AW2: The Sweet Smell of Survival
added.description: For the Lepidopterrans, putting food on the family table is never as simple as running out to the grocery store. Watch as their elite Sky Soldiers go mandible-to-mandible with fearsome Tongue Beetles in what's sure to be a hunger game for the ages!

added.title: Grey Matter AW2: Lights Out!
added.description: A reliable power supply is vital to the Galvans' around-the-clock research, so when disaster strikes, or more specifically energy-sapping parasites, these brainy beings must have an even more reliable backup plan for keeping the lights on.

added.title: Grey Matter AW1: The Archivists
added.description: Galvan Prime is home to not only the galaxy's greatest minds, but a DNA bank of every alien species in the cosmos, thus ensuring that the planet forever remains the center of DNA research for the entire universe.

added.title: Overflow AW2: Sentries of Cascareau
added.description: When the Cascan Pirates aren't plundering the depths of Cascareau for buried treasure, they're depositing their spoils into savings accounts at the Fort Knox of the high seas — a bank built atop an ever-drifting island of pontoon boats, guarded by telepathic Cephalopods, its vaults impenetrable to all but the most loyal customers.

added.title: Cannonbolt AW2: When Mega-Sharks Attack!
added.description: Arburia is well-known across the galaxy for its beach season but this year's interplanetary vacationers won't be catching many waves if the Pelarotas can't rid their waters of an unwanted visitor: the Carcharadon, a billion-toothed beast that makes Jaws look like canned tuna!

added.title: Diamondhead AW1: Great Petropian Civil War Part 1
added.description: Petropia is a planet as breathtaking and indestructible as its crystalline inhabitants, the Petropians. Occupied by many factions, a civil war broke out between the Petropians and the war-like Subsapiens from below. Little did they know, a third faction, the Antrosapians, awaited with far more sinister intentions for the kingdom.

added.title: Diamondhead AW2: Great Petropian Civil War Part  2
added.description: The Petrosapien Civil War comes to a crucial turning point as the crystalline Petrosapiens make the hard choice to team up with their warring sub-surface cousins, the Subsapiens, to defeat the monstrous Antrosapiens that dwell near Petropia's dark planetary core.

added.title: Four Arms AW2: The Warspear
added.description: A look at the perilous lengths to which the Tetramands must go in order to forge their formidable Warspears— the weapons that allow them to survive in such a savage wilderness.

added.title: Cannonbolt AW1: Beach Ballers
added.description: As the premiere vacation spot of the cosmos, Arburia is not only a sandy paradise but home to the Arburian Pelarotas. Twelve excruciatingly long hours of work and school stand between the spherical species and a day at the beach spent perfecting their cannonball!

added.title: Heatblast AW1: Extreme Season
added.description: At its molten core, Pyros is your typical planet-like star and home to the Pyronites. With rocky exteriors capable of handling these extreme conditions, observe our fiery friends as they pass the time by perfecting their pyrokinetic powers while hanging ten on the gnarliest rivers of lava.

added.title: Stinkfly AW1: The Silent Circle
added.description: The circle of life on Lepidopterra is a stinky yet harmonious effort for Lepidopterrans. The wildlife - with slime and toxic gas at their disposal - work together to maintain order on the bustling swamp planet.

added.title: Four Arms AW1: The Overlordess Games
added.description: Survival is reserved for only the strongest of warriors on Khoros, where Tetramands prove their worth by staving off savage beasts of the wild and going head-to-head inside massive gladiatorial arenas.

added.title: Shockrock AW2: Fulmanian Conquest
added.description: For the Fulmini, enough is just never enough. Traveling from planet to planet, draining worlds of their energy, this mighty race of conquerors must siphon energy from other planets in order to keep their own tapped-out planet spinning.

added.title: How to Draw Heatblast
added.description: While on a seemingly endless summer vacation with his Grandpa Max and Cousin Gwen, Ben Tennyson discovers an alien watch, the Omnitrix. This device gives Ben the ability to transform into any one of ten spectacular and powerful aliens! Ben, Gwen and Max travel the country in their motor home, affectionately known as the Rust Bucket, seeing the sights, stumbling into adventures and beating down would-be villains while generally having a blast!
